Daily Report

21 April 2023

This report is updated automatically each day to highlight key insights from the MosquitoAlertES platform. It focuses on the 6-day-ahead forecast of the Vector Risk Index (VRI) for tiger mosquitoes (Aedes albopictus) in Spain. This provides a relative measure of the variation in the risk of human contact with tiger mosquitoes across Spain and over time. The 6-day-ahead forecast (which starts on the current day) is based on the weather forecast provided daily by the Spanish Meteorological Agency.

Country-Wide Trends

During the next 7 days, we estimate the mean VRI in Spain will be 0.03 and the maximum will be 0.53, occuring on April 24 in Beniarj, Valencia/Valncia, Comunitat Valenciana. Figure 1 shows the mean and maximum values estimated for each day, starting 30-days ago and extending 6-days ahead.

Figure 1: Estimated country-wide VRI during past 30 days and coming 6 days. Red line indicates maximum values each day; blue indicates means. Vertical black dotted line shows current day.
